    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Hampden, Ohio,</name>
                    <date when="1875-03-01">March 1, 1875</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Kind sir,</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I received your card<ptr target="n5002d"/> was glad to <choice><sic>here</sic><corr>hear</corr></choice> 
                from a soldiers friend in time of need and if you are the friend that took care of me I am glad to 
                <choice><sic>here</sic><corr>hear</corr></choice> from you I can not place you as I did not learn 
                your name but havent forgot the kindness I <choice><sic>recived</sic><corr>received</corr></choice> 
                while in the <choice><sic>Army</sic><corr>Armory</corr></choice> Square Hospital<ptr target="nyp.00399_n1"/> 
                I would like to see you</p>
            <p>I draw a small <choice><sic>pencion</sic><corr>pension</corr></choice> am owing to york St[ate] grafting 
                in <choice><sic>a bout</sic><corr>about</corr></choice> 3 weeks</p>
            <p>I guess you are the friend that wrote a <choice><sic>ltter</sic><corr>letter</corr></choice> for me 
                when I first came to the hospital  I am glad to <choice><sic>here</sic><corr>hear</corr></choice> 
                from <choice><sic>eny one</sic><corr>anyone</corr></choice> write again</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>my respects and good wishes<ptr target="nyp.00398_n3"/></salute>
                <!-- No signature indicated in transcription. -->
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
